cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV

The paper describes a method for learning a probabilistic generative model of aircraft motion in terminal airspace based on a historical dataset of radar-based position measurements. This involves machine learning techniques such as fitting the model and conducting off-line performance and safety analyses. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence to predict aircraft motion, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with robotics and control systems, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves computer vision techniques to analyze the radar-based position measurements, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
